==English==
===Etymology===
< [[Medieval Latin]] ''[[timocratia]]'' < Greek ''tīmokratíā'' < ''[[tīmē]]'' valuation; honor + ''-kratíā'' a rule, reign < ''krateîn'' to rule
===Noun===
'''timocracy'''
#''Aristotelianism''. a form of government in which love of honor is the dominant motive of the rulers 
#''Platonism''. a form of government in which the ownership of property is a requirement for holding office